-- ⚠️ RE-PINNED 2026-07-14 — THE S2 INVERSION (ACCEPT/3 -> located REJECT).
-- A DEFINER shadow now WINS over the same-named interface method, unconditionally: the
-- impl universe is no longer consulted (docs/spec/SHADOW-SEMANTICS.md S2).  So
-- `size (Box 3)` no longer dispatches to `impl Sizeable Box` — it types against this
-- module`s own `size : Int -> Int` and REJECTS `Type mismatch: Int vs Box` at the call.
-- Everything below describes the OLD rule and is kept for the history only.
--
-- P0-18 (FINDINGS.md): a standalone function with the same name as an
-- interface method (documented-supported shape). check exits 0 (silent,
-- ACCEPT). `run` errors: "type error in <file>. Run `medaka check` for
-- details" (exit 1) — a dead end, since check itself reports nothing.
-- `build` agrees with check (accepts, exit 0, runs fine).
-- .expected = ACCEPT. Divergence direction: run wrongly REJECTS a program
-- check is silent on (opposite of the P0-1 bucket).
interface Sizeable a where
  size : a -> Int

data Box = Box Int

impl Sizeable Box where
  size (Box n) = n

size : Int -> Int
size n = n + 1

main = println (size (Box 3))
